 /><br />	if (something)<br />		goto somewhere;<br /><br />is actually how the CPU itself ends up executing things, while a<br /><br />	if (something) {<br />		retval = something;<br />		goto somewhere;<br />	}<br /><br />actually ends up becoming <br /><br />	if (!someting)<br />		goto over;<br />	retval = something;<br />	goto somewhere;<br />   over:<br /><br />by the time the CPU actually has to execute it.<br /><br />			Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
